an)\n|             clubs8 = \u2192 [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]] (loan)\n|             clubs9 = [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]]\n|            clubs10 = [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]]\n|            clubs11 = [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]]\n|            clubs12 = [[Thurrock F.C.|Thurrock]]\n|            clubs13 = [[East Thurrock United F.C.|East Thurrock United]]\n|            clubs14 = [[VCD Athletic F.C.|VCD Athletic]]\n|            clubs15 = [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]]\n|            clubs16 = [[Thurrock F.C.|Thurrock]]\n|              caps1 = 0 \n|             goals1 = 0\n|              caps2 = 0\n|             goals2 = 0<ref>''J.LEAGUE YEARBOOK 2001 \u2013 J\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0\u516c\u5f0f\u8a18\u9332\u96c62001'', J.League (J.League Enterprise, 2001) {{ISBN|978-4-88752-103-2}}</ref>\n|              caps3 = 79 \n|             goals3 = 1\n|              caps4 = 157 \n|             goals4 = 26\n|              caps5 = 5 \n|             goals5 = 0\n|              caps6 = 7 \n|             goals6 = 0\n|              caps7 = 13\n|             goals7 = 0\n|              caps8 = 27 \n|             goals8 = 2\n|              caps9 = 17 \n|             goals9 = 1\n|             caps10 = 17 \n|            goals10 = 0\n|             caps11 = 2\n|            goals11 = 0\n|             caps12 = ?\n|            goals12 = ?\n|             caps13 = ?\n|            goals13 = ?\n|             caps14 = ?\n|            goals14 = ?\n|             caps15 = 0\n|            goals15 = 0\n|             caps16 = ?\n|            goals16 = ?\n|     nationalyears1 = 2004\u20132006\n|      nationalteam1 = [[England C national football team|England C]]\n|      nationalcaps1 = 5 \n|     nationalgoals1 = 1\n|        club-update = 18:34, 4 November 2018 (UTC)\n|           ntupdate = \n}}\n'''Stuart Anthony Thurgood''' (born 4 November 1981) is an English former professional [[Association football|footballer]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[London Borough of Enfield|Enfield]], London, Thurgood made his debut for [[Gillingham F.C.|Gillingham]] in the 2\u20131 home win over [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] on 24 November 2007. He signed for Gillingham on a permanent basis in January 2008, keeping him at the club until 2009.<ref name=\"Exclusive: Contract Update On Four Gills Stars\">{{cite news\n| title = Exclusive: Contract Update On Four Gills Stars\n| url = http://www.gillinghamfootballclub.premiumtv.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10416~1214676,00.html\n| publisher = gillinghamfootballclub.co.uk\n| date = 14 January 2008\n| accessdate = 19 August 2008}}</ref>\n\nThurgood rejoined [[Grays Athletic F.C.|Grays Athletic]] on 13 March 2008 on [[loan (football)|loan]] until the end of the [[2007\u201308 in English football|2007\u201308]] season.<ref name=\"Player News\">{{cite news|title=Player News |url=http://www.graysathletic.co.uk/news/archives/002447.html |publisher=greysathletic.co.uk |date=19 March 2008 |access-date=19 August 2008 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080517060819/http://www.graysathletic.co.uk/news/archives/002447.html |archive-date=17 May 2008 }}</ref> He signed for Grays for a third time on 19 August 2008, on loan until the end of the [[2008\u201309 in English football|2008\u201309]] season.<ref name=\"Thurgood Back Again\">{{cite news|title=Thurgood Back Again |url=http://www.graysathletic.co.uk/news/archives/002674.html |publisher=greysathletic.co.uk |date=19 August 2008 |access-date=19 August 2008 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110809152242/http://graysathletic.co.uk/news/archives/002674.html |archive-date=9 August 2011 }}</ref> This was cut short though when he was released by Gillingham on 23 January 2009, at which point he joined Grays permanently again until the end of the season.<ref name=\"Thurgood leaves Gills\">{{cite news\n| title = Thurgood leaves Gills\n| url = http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11750_4838912,00.html\n| publisher = Sky Sports\n| date = 23 January 2009\n| accessdate = 23 January 2009}}</ref> After the end of the season, in May, he joined [[Football League Two|League Two]] team [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] on a two-year contract.<ref name=\"Daggers sign Thurgood from Grays\">{{cite news\n| title = Daggers sign Thurgood from Grays\n| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/d/dagenham_and_redbridge/8064156.stm\n| publisher = BBC Sport\n| date = 22 May 2009\n| accessdate = 22 May 2009}}</ref>\n\nDuring November 2009 he sustained an injury which eventually forced him to retire, aged just 28.<ref>{{cite news |title=Thurgood forced to retire at 28 |url=http://www.daggers.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10692~2159793,00.html |work=daggers.co.uk |publisher=[[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]] |date=20 September 2010 |accessdate=16 November 2010}}</ref>\n\nHowever, after a successful period with playing for Grays Athletic's reserve team, Thurgood signed for the [[Isthmian League]] Division One club on 11 October 2011.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.graysathletic.co.uk/news/new-signings-402249.html | title = New signings | publisher = Grays Athletic F.C. | date = 11 October 2011 | accessdate = 11 October 2011 }}</ref>\n\nIn November 2011, Thurgood signed for [[Conference South]] club [[Thurrock F.C.|Thurrock]],<ref>{{Cite web| url=http://www.footballconference.co.uk/news/details.php?news_id=5818 |title=Thurrock sign Thurgood |publisher=Football Conference |date=5 November 2011}}</ref> and returned for another spell in March 2017.\n\n==Honours==\n*[[FA Trophy]]: 2005, 2006\n*[[Conference South]] (VI): 2005\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.gillinghamfootballclub.com/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10416~9022,00.html Stuart Thurgood player profile] at gillinghamfootballclub.com\n*{{Soccerbase|24031}}\n*{{Soccerbase|36908}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Thurgood, Stuart}}\n[[Category:1981 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]